&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Mishimoto’s mission is to empower automotive enthusiasts through engineered solutions that elevate performance, reliability, and design — enabling them to push their vehicles further with confidence. Our foundation is in performance cooling, but our mission extends to any engineered product that meaningfully improves the vehicles our customers care deeply about. We build for people who are part of the car community — who modify, upgrade, and obsess over their vehicles as a form of self-expression. Our vision is to become the trusted performance partner for automotive enthusiasts worldwide.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a full-time Engineering Technician to support product development and work directly with engineers and the product team — building prototypes, testing, working on vehicles, and providing solutions to technical problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on role involving fabrication, testing, and real-work vehicle work. You’ll touch every stage of the product lifecycle- from early-stage prototype builds and testing to data collection, analysis, and install guide creation. No two days look the same; one day you’re on a lift pulling parts for an engineer, the next you’re running a pressure or heat transfer test and presenting findings to the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings mechanical aptitude, a bias towards action, and genuine enthusiasm for performance vehicles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build physical prototypes for the product engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct various experiments involving pressure, force, airflow, heat transfer, lifecycle, and destructive testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document results and present data to engineers in a clear manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect, package, and manufacture select products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create written install guides for new and existing products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove and replace (R&amp;amp;R) parts on vehicles for product engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3D scan various parts of the vehicle for space claim.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain all equipment and machines in the shop; maintain and continuously improve overall shop safety.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion growth and change for the department and the company — always excited for the next challenge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A personal passion for auto products and the industry — nobody knows what a car enthusiast wants in a product better than a car enthusiast.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a manufacturing environment, including welding, material selection, and assembly methods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong timeliness and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of Microsoft Excel, Word, and Outlook.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electromechanical experience building custom machinery or test rigs is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to use 3D modeling software; read and create 2D drawings is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with vehicles (professional or general mechanics) is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
